\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.7 Contractor and Vendor Communication Obligations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Contractors and vendors are subject to communication and documentation obligations established by this policy as a condition of access to County information systems.
 Contractors and vendors are not County employees,
 and the obligations imposed under this policy do not modify their independent contractor status.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Acknowledgment
\series default
:
 Contractors and vendors shall acknowledge the applicable provisions of this policy as a condition of access provisioning,
 in coordination with the acceptable use acknowledgment process established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Acceptable Use of Information Technology Resources Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Communication Discipline
\series default
:
 Contractors and vendors shall comply with the formal versus informal communication boundaries established in Section 6.1 and shall not act on verbal directives without written confirmation under the Written Confirmation Rule.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Boundary
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall coordinate contractor and vendor communication obligations through the contract administrator and shall not direct or supervise contractor personnel as County employees.
\end_layout

